qas.question: What does Saint Helena have the most expensive of?
What is Tungi Spirit made out of?
Ascension Island, Tristan da Cunha and Saint Helena all issue their own what?

context: Saint Helena produces what is said to be the most expensive <a0_0>coffee<a0_0/> in the world. It also produces and exports Tungi Spirit, made from the fruit of the prickly or cactus pears, <a1_0>Opuntia ficus-indica<a1_0/> ("Tungi" is the local St Helenian name for the plant). Ascension Island, Tristan da Cunha and Saint Helena all issue their own <a2_0>postage stamps<a2_0/> which provide a significant income.
